title: AREA ROUNDUP: The rematch was a mismatch
text: Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 10:03 PM By Messenger Post Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 10:03 PM Canandaigua, N.Y. SHORTSVILLE — Sean Sheets rushed for 189 yards and three touchdowns, one of two backs to rush for more than 100 yards in Red Jacket's 60-13 win over Dundee in a Section V Class D football quarterfinal on Saturday. Dan Colasurdo added 170 yards and three TDs, and Keith Rizzo added 63 yards and TD for the Indians. Andy English capped the scoring with a 57-yard TD run. Dan Brown, Tyler Gardner, Sheets and Rizzo all had interceptions for Red Jacket (7-0), which defeated Dundee (4-4) in Week 4, 41-38. Red Jacket advances to the Class D semifinals and will play Bishop Kearney (5-3) on Saturday at Webster Thomas. Game time is 1 or 4 p.m. In other high school sports action on Saturday: BOYS CROSS COUNTRY Victor’s Robert Grasso finished in first place at the Marion Cross Country Invitational. Teammate Kyle Bensink finished fourth and Justin Colucci finished 10th for the Blue Devils. Wayne’s Tanner Freida took second place, Marcus Whitman’s Gabe Stash took seventh place and Lyons’ Ethan Dietschler finished in ninth place. GIRLS CROSS COUNTRY Vanessa Morgan led Victor with a fifth place finish at the Marion Cross Country Invitational on Saturday. Red Creek’s Sydney Beach and Chloe Weaver placed seventh and eighth respectively. BOYS SOCCER CLASS C2 No. 5 Perry 4, No. 4 South Seneca/Romulus 3 Perry’s one more goal than SS/R in the first half was the difference in the game. Lincoln Backman-Lowe led SS/R with two goals and an assist and Adam Wagner added two assists. “Our kids left it all on the field,” SS/R coach Mike Johndrew said. “A tough way to end the season.” CLASS C1 No. 3 Bloomfield 2, No. 6 Williamson 1 Christian Eveleigh’s two goals led the Bombers past the Marauders. Bryce Beechler made eight saves and the Bloomfield defense held off Williamson in the second half. Seth Warren assisted on both Bloomfield goals. Bloomfield will play the winner of Red Creek and Gananda in the semifinals. CLASS B1 No. 6 Pal-Mac 3, No. 3 Hornell 2 No further stats were reported. GIRLS SOCCER No. 2 Victor 4, No. 7 Webster Thomas 0 No further stats were reported. CLASS D1 No. 2 Naples 1, No. 7 Mount Morris 0 Emma Lincoln was assisted by Mika Hobart for the only goal of the game. Ashley Wight made five saves in net. By Messenger Post
